4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under current law, a municipality, a county, or
6 a public industrial authority may abate the state and
7 local portions of certain taxes.
8 This bill would require the recommendation of
9 the Secretary of Commerce and approval of the Governor
10 for a municipality, a county, or a public industrial
11 authority to abate the state portion of these taxes.
12 This bill would make technical corrections.
13
14
15 A BILL
16 TO BE ENTITLED
17 AN ACT
18
19 Relating to abatements; to amend Section 40-9B-5, Code
20 of Alabama 1975, to prohibit a municipality, a county, or a
21 public industrial authority from abating the state portion of
22 certain taxes unless the abatement is recommended by the
23 Secretary of Commerce and approved by the Governor; and to
24 make technical corrections.
25 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
26 Section 1. Section 40-9B-5, Code of Alabama 1975, is
27 amended to read as follows:
28 "§40-9B-5
