125 (2) A municipality, a county, or a public industrial
126 authority seeking to grant an abatement of state taxes shall
127 request the abatement in writing to the Secretary of Commerce,
128 which shall include the taxes proposed to be abated, the
129 duration of the abatement, and a proposed fiscal analysis of
130 the tax loss and revenue generated.
131 (3) The secretary shall review the information provided
132 in subdivision (2) to:
133 a. Determine if the project meets any criteria set by
134 the Secretary of Commerce, including return-on-investment; and
135 b. Confirm if the company, or any related company, has
136 defaulted on a project agreement or similar agreement or any
137 economic incentive agreement at any time during the last ten
138 years.
139 (4) After the review in subdivision (3), the secretary
140 may recommend the abatement of the state taxes to the
